      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Sound of Gunfire in America</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Phil Edmunds letter says Americans have right to own guns (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Scourge of Guns'' (editorial, Sept. 5):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Scourge of Guns'' (editorial, Sept. 5):</p>
        <p>The rights of individual Americans to speak, worship and publish freely; to assemble peaceably and associate with whomever they choose; and to own firearms were recognized from the early days of the Republic. The First and Second Amendments were crafted to prohibit government from infringing on these rights.</p>
        <p>Basic freedoms enjoyed by Americans today are not gifts from government. It is absurd to suggest that individuals should be required to get a license from the government to exercise the basic right of gun ownership.</p>
        <p>PHIL EDMUNDS  Boalsburg, Pa., Sept. 6, 2000</p>
      </block>
